{"title": "Great Sea Mystery: The True Story of the \"Mary Celeste\"", "description": "On December 4, 1872, The American merchant brigantine ship \"Mary Celeste\" was found adrift and deserted, under partial sail, with lifeboat missing, off the Azores in the Atlantic Ocean. The boat was still fully provisioned, and the crew's personal belongings seemed undisturbed. None who were aboard were ever seen or heard from again. The author explores this nautical mystery and attempts to correct false rumors and rash conclusions - Summary by Mark Harrington", "duration": 10022, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "19595", "name": "John Gilbert Lockhart"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/maryceleste_2603_librivox/great_sea_mystery_2603.jpg", "copyright_year": "1930", "genres": ["Modern (19th C)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Mark Harrington"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Mark Harrington"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "mleigh"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [4100], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/maryceleste_2603_librivox/maryceleste_00_lockhart_64kb.mp3", "duration": 336}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 1:The Finding of the Ship", "readers": [4100], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/maryceleste_2603_librivox/maryceleste_01_lockhart_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1003}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 2: The \"Mary Celeste\" and Chapter 3: At Gibraltar", "readers": [4100], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/maryceleste_2603_librivox/maryceleste_02_lockhart_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1437}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter 4: Some Theories and Chapter 5: The Story of Habakuk Jephson", "readers": [4100], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/maryceleste_2603_librivox/maryceleste_03_lockhart_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1465}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapter 6: \"Solutions\" and Chapter 7: More Solutions", "readers": [4100], "pat